                    <span>Finally a book that does not spend chapters telling you how to log into MySQL and create a table. I've been heavily using MySQL for 3 years, and know a lot about it, but have still learned significant things on nearly EVERY page of this book. <P>Jeremy has a massive amount of *experience* using MySQL in real world applications, and has figured out how to communicate that in writing.<P>Buy it and read it twice.</span>
                  
              
